events.description: Titus ends the siege of Jerusalem after destroying Herod's Temple.
events.html: • 70 – Titus ends the siege of Jerusalem after destroying Herod's Temple.[1]

events.html: • 1282 – Peter III of Aragon lands at Trapani to intervene in the War of the Sicilian Vespers.

events.html: • 1363 – The five-week Battle of Lake Poyang begins, in which the forces of two Chinese rebel leaders (Chen Youliang and Zhu Yuanzhang) meet to decide who will supplant the Yuan dynasty.

events.description: Pope Paul II succeeds Pope Pius II as the 211th pope.
events.html: • 1464 – Pope Paul II succeeds Pope Pius II as the 211th pope.

events.description: Guru Ram Das becomes the Fourth Sikh Guru/Master.
events.html: • 1574 – Guru Ram Das becomes the Fourth Sikh Guru/Master.

events.description: Tokugawa Ieyasu enters Edo Castle. (Traditional Japanese date: August 1, 1590)
events.html: • 1590 – Tokugawa Ieyasu enters Edo Castle. (Traditional Japanese date: August 1, 1590)

events.description: King James VI of Scotland holds a masque at the baptism of Prince Henry at Stirling Castle.
events.html: • 1594 – King James VI of Scotland holds a masque at the baptism of Prince Henry at Stirling Castle.[3]

events.description: The Great Northern War between Sweden and Russia ends in the Treaty of Nystad.
events.html: • 1721 – The Great Northern War between Sweden and Russia ends in the Treaty of Nystad.[4]

events.description: Anne, eldest daughter of King George II of Great Britain, is given the title Princess Royal.
events.html: • 1727 – Anne, eldest daughter of King George II of Great Britain, is given the title Princess Royal.

entities.name: Anne, Princess Royal and Princess of Orange

events.description: Battle of Gross-Jägersdorf: Russian force under Field Marshal Stepan Fyodorovich Apraksin beats a smaller Prussian force commanded by Field Marshal Hans von Lehwaldt, during the Seven Years' War.
events.html: • 1757 – Battle of Gross-Jägersdorf: Russian force under Field Marshal Stepan Fyodorovich Apraksin beats a smaller Prussian force commanded by Field Marshal Hans von Lehwaldt, during the Seven Years' War.[5]

events.description: HMS Pandora sinks after having run aground on the outer Great Barrier Reef the previous day.
events.html: • 1791 – HMS Pandora sinks after having run aground on the outer Great Barrier Reef the previous day.

events.description: The entire Dutch fleet is captured by British forces under the command of Sir Ralph Abercromby and Admiral Sir Charles Mitchell during the War of the Second Coalition.
events.html: • 1799 – The entire Dutch fleet is captured by British forces under the command of Sir Ralph Abercromby and Admiral Sir Charles Mitchell during the War of the Second Coalition.

events.description: Gabriel Prosser postpones a planned slave rebellion in Richmond, Virginia, but is arrested before he can make it happen.
events.html: • 1800 – Gabriel Prosser postpones a planned slave rebellion in Richmond, Virginia, but is arrested before he can make it happen.

events.description: First Battle of Kulm: French forces are defeated by an Austrian-Prussian-Russian alliance.
events.html: • 1813 – First Battle of Kulm: French forces are defeated by an Austrian-Prussian-Russian alliance.

events.description: Creek War: Fort Mims massacre: Creek "Red Sticks" kill over 500 settlers (including over 250 armed militia) in Fort Mims, north of Mobile, Alabama.
events.html: • 1813 – Creek War: Fort Mims massacre: Creek "Red Sticks" kill over 500 settlers (including over 250 armed militia) in Fort Mims, north of Mobile, Alabama.

events.description: Australia: Melbourne, Victoria is founded.
events.html: • 1835 – Australia: Melbourne, Victoria is founded.

events.description: The city of Houston is founded by Augustus Chapman Allen and John Kirby Allen.
events.html: • 1836 – The city of Houston is founded by Augustus Chapman Allen and John Kirby Allen.[6]

events.description: American Civil War: Battle of Richmond: Confederates under Edmund Kirby Smith rout Union forces under General William "Bull" Nelson.
events.html: • 1862 – American Civil War: Battle of Richmond: Confederates under Edmund Kirby Smith rout Union forces under General William "Bull" Nelson.

events.description: Austrian explorers Julius von Payer and Karl Weyprecht discover the archipelago of Franz Josef Land in the Arctic Sea.
events.html: • 1873 – Austrian explorers Julius von Payer and Karl Weyprecht discover the archipelago of Franz Josef Land in the Arctic Sea.

events.description: Philippine Revolution: After Spanish victory in the Battle of San Juan del Monte, eight provinces in the Philippines are declared under martial law by the Spanish Governor-General Ramón Blanco y Erenas.
events.html: • 1896 – Philippine Revolution: After Spanish victory in the Battle of San Juan del Monte, eight provinces in the Philippines are declared under martial law by the Spanish Governor-General Ramón Blanco y Erenas.

entities.name: Battle of San Juan del Monte

events.description: Burgess Shale fossils are discovered by Charles Doolittle Walcott.
events.html: • 1909 – Burgess Shale fossils are discovered by Charles Doolittle Walcott.

events.description: World War I: Germans defeat the Russians in the Battle of Tannenberg.
events.html: • 1914 – World War I: Germans defeat the Russians in the Battle of Tannenberg.

events.description: Ernest Shackleton completes the rescue of all of his men stranded on Elephant Island in Antarctica.
events.html: • 1916 – Ernest Shackleton completes the rescue of all of his men stranded on Elephant Island in Antarctica.

events.description: Vietnamese prison guards led by Trịnh Văn Cấn mutiny at the Thái Nguyên penitentiary against local French authority.
events.html: • 1917 – Vietnamese prison guards led by Trịnh Văn Cấn mutiny at the Thái Nguyên penitentiary against local French authority.

events.description: Fanni Kaplan shoots and seriously injures Bolshevik leader Vladimir Lenin, which along with the assassination of Bolshevik senior official Moisei Uritsky days earlier, prompts the decree for Red Terror.
events.html: • 1918 – Fanni Kaplan shoots and seriously injures Bolshevik leader Vladimir Lenin, which along with the assassination of Bolshevik senior official Moisei Uritsky days earlier, prompts the decree for Red Terror.

events.description: Battle of Dumlupınar: The final battle in the Greco-Turkish War (Turkish War of Independence).
events.html: • 1922 – Battle of Dumlupınar: The final battle in the Greco-Turkish War (Turkish War of Independence).

events.description: The RMS Queen Mary wins the Blue Riband by setting the fastest transatlantic crossing.
events.html: • 1936 – The RMS Queen Mary wins the Blue Riband by setting the fastest transatlantic crossing.

events.description: The Second Vienna Award reassigns the territory of Northern Transylvania from Romania to Hungary.
events.html: • 1940 – The Second Vienna Award reassigns the territory of Northern Transylvania from Romania to Hungary.

events.description: The Tighina Agreement, a treaty regarding administration issues of the Transnistria Governorate, is signed between Germany and Romania.
events.html: • 1941 – The Tighina Agreement, a treaty regarding administration issues of the Transnistria Governorate, is signed between Germany and Romania.[7]

events.description: World War II: The Battle of Alam el Halfa begins.
events.html: • 1942 – World War II: The Battle of Alam el Halfa begins.

events.description: The Japanese occupation of Hong Kong comes to an end.
events.html: • 1945 – The Japanese occupation of Hong Kong comes to an end.

events.description: The Supreme Commander of the Allied Forces, General Douglas MacArthur lands at Atsugi Air Force Base.
events.html: • 1945 – The Supreme Commander of the Allied Forces, General Douglas MacArthur lands at Atsugi Air Force Base.

events.description: The Allied Control Council, governing Germany after World War II, comes into being.
events.html: • 1945 – The Allied Control Council, governing Germany after World War II, comes into being.

events.description: South Vietnamese opposition figure Phan Quang Dan was elected to the National Assembly despite soldiers being bussed in to vote for President Ngo Dinh Diem's candidate.

events.description: Japan conducts a test of the NAMC YS-11, its first aircraft since World War II and its only successful commercial aircraft from before or after the war.
events.html: • 1962 – Japan conducts a test of the NAMC YS-11, its first aircraft since World War II and its only successful commercial aircraft from before or after the war.

events.description: The Moscow–Washington hotline between the leaders of the U.S. and the Soviet Union goes into operation.
events.html: • 1963 – The Moscow–Washington hotline between the leaders of the U.S. and the Soviet Union goes into operation.

events.description: A Belgrade–Dortmund express train derails at the main train station in Zagreb killing 153 passengers.
events.html: • 1974 – A Belgrade–Dortmund express train derails at the main train station in Zagreb killing 153 passengers.

events.description: A powerful bomb explodes at the Mitsubishi Heavy Industries headquarters in Marunouchi, Tokyo. Eight are killed, 378 are injured. Eight left-wing activists are arrested on May 19, 1975, by Japanese authorities.
events.html: • 1974 – A powerful bomb explodes at the Mitsubishi Heavy Industries headquarters in Marunouchi, Tokyo. Eight are killed, 378 are injured. Eight left-wing activists are arrested on May 19, 1975, by Japanese authorities.

events.description: The Third World Population Conference ends in Bucharest, Romania. At the end of the ceremony, the UN-Romanian Demographic Centre is inaugurated.

events.html: • 1981 – President Mohammad-Ali Rajai and Prime Minister Mohammad-Javad Bahonar of Iran are assassinated in a bombing committed by the People's Mujahedin of Iran.
